listProblem.detailsInfo:
Reports assignment operations which can be replaced by operator-assignment.

Code using operator assignment is shorter and may be clearer.

**Example:**

      x = x + 3;
      x = x / 3;

After the quick fix is applied:

      x += 3;
      x /= 3;


Use the **Ignore conditional operators** option to ignore `&&`
and `||`. Replacing conditional operators with operator
assignment would change the evaluation from lazy to eager, which may change the semantics of the expression.


Use the **Ignore obscure operators** option to ignore `^` and `%`, which are less known.

code.surroundingCode:
Random random = new Random(key.toString().hashCode());
for (int i = 0; i < out.length; i++)
    out[i] = (char) (out[i] >> key.charAt(random.nextInt(key.reverse().length())) % 8);
if (out.length % 2 != 0)
    key.reverse();

